TruthGuardEnv v1.0 — System Overview
Problem Statement:-
Modern consumers rely on product labels such as “natural”, “chemical-free”, or “non-toxic”, but these claims are often misleading or unverifiable without expert knowledge.We are working on cosmetic products.

In real-world workflows, professionals such as:-
regulatory auditors
product safety analysts
e-commerce compliance teams
must manually inspect ingredient lists, verify claims, and assess risk under incomplete or uncertain information.

This process is:-
time-consuming
error-prone
dependent on domain expertise

Solution Overview:-
TruthGuardEnv is an OpenEnv-compliant simulation environment that models this real-world task as a step-by-step AI auditing process.

Instead of making a one-shot prediction, an AI agent must:-
Investigate product ingredients
Verify marketing claims
Handle missing or noisy information
Incrementally update its internal belief
Produce a final safety verdict

Real-World Task Simulation:-
This environment simulates a product safety auditing workflow, which directly maps to real industry use cases:-
E-commerce platforms → filtering misleading product listings
Regulatory bodies → auditing compliance claims
Dermatology & safety tools → assessing ingredient risks
Consumer protection systems → identifying deceptive labeling

The task is not artificial — it replicates how humans investigate, verify, and decide under uncertainty.
